## 1. Security Validation
**Objective:** To ensure that the infrastructure is hardened against unauthorized access and follows the principle of least privilege.

| Test Case ID | Test Category | Procedure | Expected Result | Status |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| **SEC-01** | **Network Isolation** | Attempt to SSH into an EC2 instance using a Public IP (if any) or from a non-authorized network. | Connection should time out/be refused. Only Admin IP via SSH should work if properly configured, but ideally, private instances have no public IPs. | [ ] |
| **SEC-02** | **ALB Security** | Access the website using the ALB DNS: `http://a3-g7-csvc-alb-51735129.us-east-1.elb.amazonaws.com/` | Homepage (index.php) should load successfully. | [ ] |
| **SEC-03** | **DB Isolation** | Attempt to connect to the RDS endpoint `a3-g7-csvc-rds.cyqrkpjiqi18.us-east-1.rds.amazonaws.com` from a local machine using MySQL Workbench. | Connection should fail as the RDS is in a private subnet with a security group only allowing access from EC2 instances. | [ ] |
| **SEC-04** | **Inbound Rules** | Check Security Group `A3-G7-CSVC-ALB-SG` in AWS Console. | Only Port 80 (HTTP) should be open to `0.0.0.0/0`. | [ ] |
| **SEC-05** | **Parameter Store** | Check if DB credentials are NOT hardcoded in PHP but fetched via SSM Parameter Store. | Sensitive data like `db_password` should be encrypted (SecureString). | [ ] |

