## 2. High Availability (HA) Validation
**Objective:** To verify that the system remains functional during unexpected component failures.

| Test Case ID | Test Category | Procedure | Expected Result | Status |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| **HA-01** | **Instance Failover** | Manually **Terminate** one EC2 instance in the Auto Scaling Group via the AWS Console. | The ALB should stop sending traffic to the terminated instance. Within minutes, the ASG should launch a replacement instance. | [ ] |
| **HA-02** | **Multi-AZ ALB** | Check ALB configuration. | ALB should have subnets in both `us-east-1a` and `us-east-1b`. | [ ] |
| **HA-03** | **RDS Failover** | Perform a **Reboot with Failover** on the RDS instance `a3-g7-csvc-rds`. | The database endpoint should remain the same. The application should re-establish connection to the new primary instance with minimal downtime (< 60s). | [ ] |
| **HA-04** | **Target Group Health** | View Target Group `A3-G7-CSVC-TG`. | All registered targets should show status `healthy`. | [ ] |

