## 3. Scalability Validation
**Objective:** To confirm that the system handles fluctuating load by adjusting resources automatically.

| Test Case ID | Test Category | Procedure | Expected Result | Status |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| **SCA-01** | **Load-Based Scaling** | Log into an EC2 instance and run a stress tool: `sudo yum install stress -y` then `stress --cpu 2 --timeout 300s`. | CPU utilization should spike. Once it crosses the threshold (e.g., 70%), the ASG should launch additional instances up to the Max capacity. | [ ] |
| **SCA-02** | **Scale In Policy** | Stop the stress test and wait for 5-10 minutes. | Once CPU drops, the ASG should terminate the extra instances, returning to the Desired/Minimum capacity. | [ ] |
| **SCA-03** | **Distribution** | Rapidly refresh the homepage. | Requests should be distributed across different instances (verify by checking logs or adding `hostname` to the PHP footer). | [ ] |

